The `MapDemeaner` and `WithinDemeaner` backends accept `fixef_tol` and `fixef_maxiter`
arguments to control convergence. The `WithinDemeaner` additionally accepts `krylov`,
`preconditioner`, and `gmres_restart` (used only with `krylov="gmres"`). The
`preconditioner` argument accepts `"additive"`, `"multiplicative"`, and `"off"`;
`"off"` matches `within.Preconditioner.Off`. For compatibility with `scipy`, the
`LsmrDemeaner` has two arguments to control the convergence tolerance - `fixef_atol`
and `fixef_btol`.

::: {#b8f84436 .cell execution_count=3}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit = pf.feols(
    "Y ~ X1 | f1",
    data=df,
    demeaner=MapDemeaner(backend="rust", fixef_tol=1e-10, fixef_maxiter=50_000),
)
```
:::
